iors?</span><hr size=1> Gear for the 35-55 crowd is not only not needed, it's counter-productive.  I know I'm not alone in my view that there's lots and lots and lots and lots of gear available for the 35-55, or the 1-60 crowd, and making it any easier simply deprives people at those levels of any sort of a challenge.   <br>
<br>
I may sound like an old man, but when I, and many others on this board were in those levels, the obscene amount and quality of equipment was nowhere near where it is today.   There were no Frostbringers, Ornate Swords, Snowchippers, Fleshgrinders, Centi Short Swords, Centi Longswords, and WORSE, Windblades, there was no Crustacean Shell armor!<br>
<br>
Those from my era were using SSOY's at level 50, we quested our own crafted armor, when we moved on to Kunark, we hunted for our equipment, using it when it dropped.   I remember getting a 17/30 shimmering Partisan and it was GODLY in the offhand to go along with my Jarsath Trident that I was using as a combo at 55 while still doing hate on a regular basis watching mummy after mummy not dropping anything.<br>
<br>
Those in the lower levels need something to look forward to, not an even EASIER time levelling up.  Currently, my lower level bretheren have it FAR easier than most of us did when we were doing the grinds to 50 and then to 60, and I for one am not interested in making it even easier through more mudflation, making this into a shallow, challenge-free game where the greatest rewards are found in playing the bazaar game right.    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jerychowahlsov>Jerycho Wahlsov</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/22/02 12:39:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2517.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Improve or not the warriors?</span><hr size=1> I agree that there is an over-abundance of quality gear available for the 35-60 crowd today.<br>
<br>
But this is the inevitable result of a very bad basic design flaw with this game, which is this: all items are persistent.<br>
<br>
Think about it, when someone's used their crafted armor for 20 levels, it should be SHOT. It should be so beat up as to be unusable by anyone else without a significant amount of smithing -- and expensive smithing at that!<br>
<br>
But that isn't how the game works. The game works by making every item that comes into the world last effectively forever. The only way the game designers have of not having an item have an infinite life-span is to make it no-drop. <br>
<br>
It's really a bad situation that arises from a bad design decission that is tied very tightly to the core of the game database. <br>
<br>
So the result is that people in the early levels are grossly over-equiped for thier level AND (and this is the important part) when people do get into the &quot;uber&quot; levels they start thinking that they should have BETTER gear to obtain.<br>
<br>
But the problem is, they've been in full cobalt with a fleshgrinder since level 35. That's GOOD gear for a level 65 warrior. The only reason it's not viewed as good gear is because of mudflation. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mahulkkeras>Mahulk Keras</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/22/02 1:18:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2517.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Improve or not the warriors?</span><hr size=1> Full cobalt is good when you are fighting in Kunark and Velious... gear goes with the mobs you fight... <p>&lt;a href=http://212.73.29.131/familjen/dspMember.php?Name=Mahulk target=blank&gt;Mahulk Keras&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;<br>
